entry.def: If something discolours or if it is discoloured by something else, its original colour changes, so that it looks unattractive.

example.ex: A tooth which has been hit hard may discolour...
example.tran: 受过重击的牙齿可能会变色。

example.ex: Some oil had seeped out, discolouring the grass.
example.tran: 有些油渗出来了，把草地染得变了颜色。

means.word_mean: 2. the act of changing the natural color of something by making it duller or dingier or unnatural or faded
